paragraph.value: The distribution of their named-entity (NE) tags, according to Stanford NE-tagger, is shown in Table 1. While temporal-related numbers are the most frequent, around 40% are classified only as unspecific NUMBER. By manually checking 100 random NUMBERs, we observed that 47 are relation cardinalities,1 i.e., approximately 18.86% of all numbers in Wikipedia are relation cardinalities.
